
[1]basil

   BAS'IL, n. s as z. The slope or angle of a tool or instrument as of a
   chisel or plane; usually of 12 degrees, but for hard wood, 18 degrees.

   BAS'IL, v.t. To grind or form the edge of a tool to an angle.

   BAS'IL, n. s as z.

   1. A plant of the genus Ocymum, of which there are many species, all
   natives of warm climates. They are fragrant aromatic plants, and one
   species, the sweet basil, is much used in cookery, especially in
   France.

         BAS'IL, n. The skin of a sheep tanned; written also basan.
